===Grey Cup=== {| class="wikitable" ! Team !! Q1 !! Q2 !! Q3 !! Q4 !! Total |-style="background-color:#DDFFDD" |[[Saskatchewan Roughriders]] || 0 || 10 || 6 || 7 || '''23''' |- |[[Winnipeg Blue Bombers]] || 3 || 4 || 7 || 5 || 19 |} <ref name="nationalpost.com">[http://www.nationalpost.com/sports/story.html?id=123061 Green glory: Riders win sloppy Grey Cup<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
Saskatchewan ended the [[Canadian Football League]]'s longest championship drought with a 23â19 victory over the Winnipeg Blue Bombers in the [[95th Grey Cup]] at [[Rogers Centre]]. The Roughriders had not won a title since [[77th Grey Cup|1989]], and had lost in 13 of their 15 all-time appearances.<ref name="nationalpost.com"/>
An interception by defensive back [[James Johnson]] with 54 seconds left in the fourth quarter sealed the victory. It also earned Johnson a place in CFL history â because he became the first player to intercept three passes in a Grey Cup game, and also because he was named the game's [[Grey Cup Most Valuable Player|MVP]].<ref name="nationalpost.com"/> Roughriders receiver Andy Fantuz was named the game's [[Dick Suderman Trophy|Most Outstanding Canadian]]. The 23-year-old caught four passes for 70 yards and a touchdown.<ref name="nationalpost.com"/>
==Awards and Records== * Kent Austin, [[Annis Stukus Trophy|CFL Coach of the Year]] * Kerry Joseph, [[CFL's Most Outstanding Player Award|Most Outstanding Player Award]] * Kerry Joseph, [[Jeff Nicklin Memorial Trophy]] * James Johnson, [[Grey Cup Most Valuable Player]] * James Johnson, first player to intercept three passes in a Grey Cup game * Andy Fantuz, [[Dick Suderman Trophy|Grey Cup Most Outstanding Canadian]]
